#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:669
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>learn</userinput><indexterm><primary>learn</primary></indexterm> "
"is special as it is used to create your own commands. The commands you "
"create can take <glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">input</glossterm> and "
"return <glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">output</glossterm>. Let us take a "
"look at how a new command is created: <screen>\n"
"learn circle $x {\n"
"  repeat 36 {\n"
"    forward $x\n"
"    turnleft 10\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> The new command is called <userinput>circle</userinput>. "
"<userinput>circle</userinput> takes one <glossterm linkend=\"input-output"
"\">input</glossterm> argument, to set the size of the circle. "
"<userinput>circle</userinput> returns no <glossterm linkend=\"input-output"
"\">output</glossterm>. The <userinput>circle</userinput> command can now be "
"used like a normal command in the rest of the code. See this example:"
msgstr ""
"<userinput> </userinput> ni A Bidasanzwe command , ni Byakoreshejwe Kuri "
"Kurema Amabwiriza . command Kurema < = \" Iyinjiza - Ibisohoka \" > Iyinjiza "
"< /> na Garuka < = \" Iyinjiza - Ibisohoka \" > Ibisohoka < /> . RW A Kureba "
"Ku A Gishya command ni Byaremwe : <screen> \n"
"Uruziga x [ \n"
"Gusubiramo [ \n"
"Imbere ] \n"
"] \n"
"</screen> Gishya command ni <userinput> Uruziga </userinput> . <userinput> "
"Uruziga </userinput> Rimwe < = \" Iyinjiza - Ibisohoka \" > Iyinjiza < /> , "
"A Umubare , Kuri Gushyiraho i Ingano: Bya i Uruziga . <userinput> Uruziga </"
"userinput> Oya < = \" Iyinjiza - Ibisohoka \" > Ibisohoka < /> . <userinput> "
"Uruziga </userinput> command NONEAHA Byakoreshejwe nka A Bisanzwe command in "
"i Bya i Inyandikoporogaramu . iyi Urugero: : "

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:672
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"learn circle $X {\n"
"  repeat 36 {\n"
"    forward $X \n"
"    turnleft 10 \n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"go 200,200 \n"
"circle 20\n"
"\n"
"go 300,200 \n"
"circle 40"
msgstr ""
"Uruziga [ \n"
"Gusubiramo [ \n"
"Imbere \n"
"10 \n"
"] \n"
"] \n"
"\n"
"Gyayo , \n"
"Uruziga , \n"
"Uruziga 50% "

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:674
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the next example, a command with a return<indexterm><primary>return</"
"primary></indexterm> value is created. <screen>\n"
"learn faculty $x {\n"
"  $r = 1\n"
"  for $i = 1 to $x {\n"
"    $r = $r * $i\n"
"  }\n"
"  return $r\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"print faculty 5\n"
"</screen> In this example a new command called <userinput>faculty</"
"userinput> is created. If the input of this command is <userinput>5</"
"userinput> then the output is <userinput>5*4*3*2*1</userinput>. By using "
"<userinput>return</userinput> the <glossterm linkend=\"input-output"
"\">output</glossterm> value is specified and the execution is returned."
msgstr ""
"i Ibikurikira > Urugero: , A command Na: A Garuka Agaciro: ni Byaremwe . "
"<screen> \n"
"n [ \n"
"r = n * r = n * Garuka ] \n"
"i = \" Injiza A Umubare na Kanda \" \n"
"&Shyira ku rupapuro... i + \" ku ni : \" + </screen> iyi Urugero: A Gishya "
"command <userinput> </userinput> ni Byaremwe . Iyinjiza Bya iyi command ni "
"ku na Hanyuma , ikoresha i < Agafashi ID = \" Garuka \" /> <userinput> "
"Garuka </userinput> command . <userinput> Garuka </userinput> command ni i "
"Kuri Ibisohoka A Agaciro: Kuva: A Umumaro Byaremwe . "

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:677
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Commands can have more than one <glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">input</"
"glossterm>. In the next example, a command that draws a rectangle is "
"created: <screen>\n"
"learn box $x, $y {\n"
"  forward $y\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"  forward $x\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"  forward $y\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"  forward $x\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> Now you can run <userinput>box 50, 100</userinput> and the turtle "
"will draw a rectangle on the canvas."
msgstr ""

